<paragraph id="25849860F2B91161F55FB478F323B6CE" pageId="5" pageNumber="16">
<bibRefCitation id="8F62E104A5E0CD01A3D2DD9DF1C5F4A7" author="Moldenke, AR" journalOrPublisher="Frey" pageId="60" pageNumber="71" pagination="75 - 116" title="A Generic reclassification of the New World Clytrinae (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae). Entomologische Arbeiten aus dem Museum G." volume="29" year="1981">Moldenke (1981)</bibRefCitation>
, divided 
<taxonomicName id="33E9A66B035A2E0F21C565BCA6061768" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Babia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Babia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Babia</taxonomicName>
into six subgenera based on morphological features, such as the general shape of the body, pronotal margin, frons and antennomere morphology: 
<taxonomicName id="1628C02CFD582F2690468AB0DE8E2399" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Babia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Babia (Babia)" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Babia">Babia (Babia)</taxonomicName>
Chevrolat and 
<taxonomicName id="C38A0D9749DB1A47E2B8D933465CDFBB" genus="B." lsidName="B. (Archaebabia)" pageId="5" pageNumber="16" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Archaebabia">B. (Archaebabia)</taxonomicName>
Moldenke from America north of Mexico; 
<taxonomicName id="C18054894E19FD849BCC1632BFEC4883" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Babia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Babia (Coleolacordairei)" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Coleolacordairei">Babia (Coleolacordairei)</taxonomicName>
Moldenke, 
<taxonomicName id="AD727C2245D38E2F5991084282925CF0" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Babia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Babia (Heterobabia)" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Heterobabia">Babia (Heterobabia)</taxonomicName>
Moldenke, and 
<taxonomicName id="6D5763CFB02E47774FCC7291A01C7524" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Babia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Babia (Megababia)" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Megababia">Babia (Megababia)</taxonomicName>
Moldenke from the Neotropical region. Only the monotypic 
<taxonomicName id="A4FA96861876291540DA4336258E578B" genus="B." lsidName="B. (Coleolacordairei)" pageId="5" pageNumber="16" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Coleolacordairei">B. (Coleolacordairei)</taxonomicName>
is represented in Argentina.
</paragraph>
